headlines.description: — Gabe Vincent scored 27 points, Bam Adebayo had 20 points and 13 rebounds and the Miami Heat beat the Milwaukee Bucks 111-95 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vincent leads Heat to 2nd straight win over Bucks

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 17 of his 33 points in a pivotal third quarter, Malcolm Brogdon added 30 points and the Boston Celtics beat the Charlotte Hornets 122-106 on Saturday night to push their winning streak to six.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Celtics roll past Hornets for 6th straight victory

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 23 points, 10 assists and another ferocious dunk, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Indiana Pacers 130-112 on Saturday night to extend...
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant's slam in Indy highlights Grizzlies' 9th straight win

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 29 points, Dejounte Murray had 27 and the Atlanta Hawks never trailed in a 114-103 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 29, Murray 27 as Hawks beat Raptors 114-103

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 26 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves got a huge boost from their bench in a 110-102 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, bench lift Wolves to 110-102 victory over Cavs

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid made a jumper with 5.7 seconds left to lift the Philadelphia 76ers to a 118-117 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's jumper gives 76ers 118-117 win over Jazz

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 36 points and 10 assists, and the Portland Trail Blazers snapped a five-game losing streak with a 136-119 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 32 and Blazers beat Mavs 136-119 to end skid
